==English==

===Etymology===
Referring to a time when, if [[chimney sweep]]s were afraid to ascend a chimney, the fire would be lit under them in order to motivate them to climb to the top.

===Verb===
{{head|en|verb|head=[[light]] [[a]] [[fire]] [[under]] (someone)}}

# {{lb|en|idiomatic}} To [[motivate]] or encourage (someone) to start sooner or move faster.
#: ''Let me see if I can '''light a fire under''' the waiter to get our order sooner.''